SOA detail: drop zero-list-price junk lines + reset script for batch re-test

A test order surfaced a Combination line at ZERO list price next to its
actual paid services (Hair Cut 540 / Filipino Traditional 1080) on the
same Yuna in one SOA. order_items has no parent/child relation -- it's
just a flat junk row whose list_price_cents = 0. Real services always
carry a list price; DIS-90 nets to 0 but list stays positive, so the
filter "list_price_cents > 0" cleanly drops placeholders without hiding
legitimate 100%-discount lines.

- soa/actions.ts:toSoaOrderLine -- filter chains 0-list-price out
  alongside cancelled status. Shared by Generate workspace + History
  detail so both views match the SOA PDF.
- soa-pdf.tsx -- mirror the same filter (and add list_price_cents to
  the order_items select so the column is available).

Reset helper for re-testing the new one-journal batch-settle path:

- scripts/reset-settled-soas-for-batch-test.mjs flips the three SOAs
  that were posted as 3 separate Acumatica journals (F00188170/171/172)
  back to issued: clears gl_batch_nbr / posting_status / posting_error,
  restores outstanding_cents = total_cents. Order links are kept so the
  same SOAs reappear in AR Balance. Lists open intercompany SOAs grouped
  by branch afterwards so it's visible up front how many journals the
  next batch-settle will produce (3 SOAs / 1 branch -> 1 journal).

